        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 2:48AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 247 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Davis Junction to near Oregon. Movement
was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Milford, Oregon, Byron, Lindenwood, Kirkland, Davis Junction,
Kingston, Fairdale, Kings, Chana, Malta, DeKalb, Monroe Center,
Sycamore, Cortland, Hillcrest, Creston, Genoa, Stillman Valley,
Rochelle, Maple Park, and Rockford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
